`true` if this card will be an instant-issued debit card ready for eCommerce activity that can also be provisioned to a digital wallet. If `true` the card will be created with a `status` of `DitalActivePhysicalInitiated` which will shortly change to `DigitalActivePhysicalPending`. When card is in `DigitalActivePhysicalInitiated` or `DigitalActivePhysicalPending` it can be provisioned into a digital wallet via [/card/provision/applePay](https://docs.helix.q2.com/reference/cardprovisionapplepay) or [/card/provision/googlePay](https://docs.helix.q2.com/reference/cardprovisiongooglepay). When card is in `DigitalActivePhysicalPending` it will need to be verified via [/card/verify](https://docs.helix.q2.com/reference/cardverify) before a customer can use the physical card.
`true` to order a physical card, `false` to waive.

For Shazam programs only. Visa DPS programs must call the [/card/resetPin](https://docs.helix.q2.com/reference/cardresetpin) endpoint separately. For physical-only cards, /card/resetPin can be called once the card moves from `status=Initiated` to `status=Verified`. For dual-issuance cards (physical and digital), /card/resetPin can be called once the card moves from `status=Initiated` to `status=DigitalActivePhysicalPending`.

- `FirstPartyFraud`: When someone uses his/her own identity to obtain products and services with no intent to fulfill their payment obligation.
- `ThirdPartyFraud`: When someone uses a stolen identity to commit fraud. Refers to fraud that is committed without the knowledge of the person whose identity is used to commit the fraud. 
- `SyntheticIdFraud`: When someone uses a possible combination of real and phony attributes, including possible real attributes that don’t correlate to each other, in order to assemble a phony identity. This information is then used to open fraudulent accounts and/or obtain goods and services.
- `AccountTakeoverFraud`: When someone uses another person's account information to make purchases or withdraw money and often involves changing credentials and/or personal profile information. 
- `NonActivity`: Non-Activity.
- `BankDiscretion`: Bank chose to archive for a non-fraud reason
- `Other`: Default value. Providing a detailed reason is strongly encouraged as it informs and improves fraud detection mechanisms.
